annotation.TEXT: 21 coins... I think I could've done better than that.
However, you do have to burn a jump to get that Yoshi coin, but it might be worth it, because you do have a little leeway with your allotted jumps.
Ooh, an opportunity to do that bubble glitch!
Okay, so in this level, we play as Yoshi (indicated by the "Y" in the status bar), and the goal is to rescue Mario.
Hey there Wiggler.
Instead, you're forced to solve this ridiculously easy P-switch puzzle (and optionally glitch fish into existence and eat them).
Wow, that's strange. Usually, Peach is the one that Bowser kidnaps! How'd he get the jump on Mario?
Be careful, because you still have Yoshi's slightly larger hitbox here! But, at least you can still walk on top of munchers safely and murder stuff with your stomps!
And there's Mario! Now, you can just tear through these six cement blocks for some reason.
Also, I'll take this shell with me, just because I can.
Oh, that was interesting. (Although it was a bit picky with my position as I was trying to enter.)
Well, I guess Mario's grounded, as a punishment for letting himself get kidnapped by Bowser!
Oh, yeah. Watch out, because the Rhinos are immune to shell attacks! Also, watch out for their fire breath if you give them a chance to use it.
Whoa! That guy almost got me! And there appears to be another Yoshi coin that I'd have to use up an additional jump for. Still, I think I can spare one more.
Up next will be the Red Switch Palace!
Not the reset door, though. I mean one of the gimmicky doors.
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x! After considering the hack requests I've received, I've decided on this one to play next, which is...
Oh, really? WYE put a blue koopa in a Yoshi-only level? Now I can easily break the level by just flying over the top-- Oh.
Yeah, not happening. Maybe if I was patient I could've gotten a 1-up combo a bit to the left, but whatever.
Now, I know I can do better than 8 coins on a 4-high multi-coin block...
I guess you could hang onto the blue shell and fly around afterwards, but the ceiling is still there, so just remember that. Still, I guess you could fly over some obstacles.
Good question. Where is Mario? Find out next time! To be continued...
Yep, WYE thought of that. So, you can't break the level that way!
Yoshi plays just like he normally would, except you can't spin jump or dismount (for obvious reasons), and if you take a single hit, you die.
I guess I have to wait for the P-switch to expire to proceed.
..."A Strange Mission", with very colorful letters! And, apparently, this hack was made in 2009 by White-White-Green-Yoshi-White-Egg! (Actually, it's just "WhiteYoshiEgg"!)
That's all I could get? Well, it kind of has to be at just the right height to get 1-ups out of it...
Ah, but it's called the Colorful Coin Palace. What "get-rich-quick-to-possibly-bribe-somebody-with" scheme will I encounter in there? Find out next time!
Mario's so awesome at collecting coins while travelling through doors. Also, I guess I can't get that 1-up until after I activate the Red Switch Palace, which will redirect where that door takes me.
You didn't really fall for that, did you?
Yeah, so when you enter a door in this level, you get shifted towards an exit door to the right. (The exit doors can't be entered however. Only the "entrance" doors can.)
Oh, yeah, and as the message indicated, you can Start+Select out of this level at any time, even if you haven't cleared it yet.
Speaking of flying, I think you absolutely have to here (unless you do something insane or TAS-worthy like wall jumping).
It would take an additional jump to get those two coins above, which totally isn't worth it.
Yeah, it gives you the "no good" sound effect and won't let you in, so you'll have to release whatever you're holding to enter one of those doors.
If you've spent all your jumps, you don't instantly die, but...
Okay, I'm going to try to hang onto this shell until I reach the next door so that I can show you what happens if you try to enter a door while holding something.
Now, there is indeed a secret exit in this level, but that'll have to wait until later.
Don't jump straight for this Yoshi coin right away, or you'll fall to your doom. Instead, make use of the rotating platform to get it safely.
So, let's begin on a new file here...
Oh, that's neat how even the P-switch door gets in on the act!
Whoa, that was close! Try to save a few jumps by bouncing off of enemies.
Gee, I wonder where a P-switch door will appear...

So, the doors force me to the right (and down whenever possible) until I hit a gray door, and I think the walls that I pass through are made up of custom blocks that don't let me through unless I'm in "going through a door" mode. Still, it's pretty neat.
Now, before I start the next level, you're probably wondering what happens when you run out of jumps. Let's find out!
I still had two jumps to spare, and I know I could've saved at least two jumps by not going for Yoshi coins. I wonder what the actual minimum number of jumps this level requires is...
Yeah, learnin' about reset pipes and doors.
Also, we've got super koopas flying around here, but that's pretty much it for the title screen.
Now, just so you guys know, I've actually played through this hack before (well before it was requested), so this will not be a blind run.
...you effectively can't jump anymore. If you're not already right in front of the goal by this point, you'll have to Start+Select out (or kill yourself somehow).
Blugh! Too spicy.
Judging by the "No Mario" sign, I'd say we're getting close.
And there's the last Yoshi coin.
May as well get that Yoshi coin while jumping here. And there's the goal. If you have at least one jump left, try for a high number of stars.
Hmm... I'll come back to that door in a moment. Also, did you notice how my fireball went through the walls to the right of the door? I smell custom blocks at work here!
Also, that blue koopa slipped through the slope for some reason, but whatever.
Okay, next level, and it's a red one. Hmm...
Can I eat Mario? No? Aw, nuts. Touch Mario to finish the level.

You might have heard of or seen minimal jump challenges before, right? Well, that's the gimmick of this level. You're only allowed to jump 15 times (shown in the upper-right corner), so don't waste them!
To be continued...
I thought about trying to conserve one jump here, but decided not to risk it (though it might've been possible).
Yeah, collectin' coins while slidin' back an' forth.
This part may look tricky, but it's really not.
Goal! And I get another 40 stars (which is par for the course), and a 1-up from the Bob-omb.
Oh, yeah. And you can't be holding anything when you try to enter these doors.
Whoa there, Dino-Rhino!
40 stars, and an extra mushroom since I brought the shell with me. Not bad.
And here's our first door of the forest...
